[Plot]

A man regains consciousness at the bottom of a deep,
dark cave with no recollection of how he got there--much
less what happened to the dead man beside him. His only
hope of escape is to head towards the surface through a
seemingly never-ending network of tunnels inhabited by
strange and terrifying creatures. It&#039;s here in the subterranean
depths that Tolbiac (Clovis Cornillac, A VERY LONG ENGAGEMENT)
discovers the existence of a mysterious society known only as
Eden Log. Franck Vestiel&#039;s futuristic thriller boasts some
wonderfully atmospheric visuals that call to mind the works
of Luc Besson, Marc Caro and Jean-Pierre Jeunet, and
early Darren Aronofsky.
